mindmap
  root((AI Strategy Roadmapping))
    Core Elements
      Business objectives and transformation themes
      Prioritized use cases tied to KPIs
      Technical enablers and data dependencies
      Time-phased delivery sequencing
    Sequencing Discipline
      Business value vs technical feasibility
      Early wins as credibility builders
      Pipeline of next-stage opportunities
      Political navigation and sponsor alignment
      Interdependency coordination
    Scaffolding Layers
      Governance
        Ethical reviews built into timeline
        Fairness audits and compliance gates
        Predictable partner not blocker
      Talent
        Role forecasting by phase
        Internal vs external staffing
        Scale planning as use cases mature
      Tooling
        MLOps and CI/CD alignment
        Observability for LLM systems
        Infrastructure of trust
    Stakeholder Alignment
      Co-creation through workshops and steering committees
      Tailored views for different audiences
        C-suite - themes ROI risks
        Technical - specs dependencies tooling
        Business units - workflow enablement
      Structured checkpoints and review cycles
    Visualization
      Timeline grouped by transformation theme
      Interdependencies mapped explicitly
      Decision gates and milestones
      Layered views for multiple audiences
    Living Document
      Quarterly strategic reviews
      Recalibrate assumptions and sequencing
      Feedback loops from deployment learning
      Course correction without blame
    Common Pitfalls
      Overloading early phases
      Ignoring data and platform dependencies
      Treating the roadmap as fixed
      Building in isolation
      Disconnecting from decision cycles